pan>
<p local-id=3D"6fd2cabcdee8"></p>
<p local-id=3D"c8fadee601f2">Actors:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a46189d8655f">DevOps Intern: Primary actor responsible for a=
ll setup and validation tasks</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"79539f345c29" id=3D"Task22-RAD-3.2UseCases">3.2 Use Cases</=
h3>
<hr>
<h4 local-id=3D"9d24240df766" id=3D"Task22-RAD-3.2.1UseCase1:InstallandConf=
igureGitLabCEonEC2">3.2.1 Use Case 1: Install and Configure GitLab CE on EC=
2</h4>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"99b5cf4b5a53"><strong>Description:</strong> The DevOps inter=
n provisions an EC2 instance and installs GitLab CE on it, making the web i=
nterface accessible via the instance's public IP or DNS.</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4ebf5016d0d2"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Intern, AWS EC=
2 Instance</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c006cec801ce"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fa02c441f6f8">AWS account is active and EC2 access is availa=
ble</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d2ef15de507e">EC2 instance (Ubuntu 20.04/22.04, t2.medium or=
 higher) is running</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8578f0806918">Security Group allows inbound traffic on ports=
 22, 80, and 443</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"37b7c9340ad7">SSH key pair is available for EC2 access</p></=
li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6f280ba27d65"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"509f4eb75b16">GitLab CE is installed and running on the EC2 =
instance</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5c080e2b1e78">GitLab web interface is accessible via the EC2=
 public IP on port 80 or 443</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"defeecd1cd3e">GitLab services (nginx, puma, sidekiq, etc.) a=
re active and healthy</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"78300ef18873"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"74794f1edcf3">DevOps intern launches an EC2 instance with Ub=
untu OS</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d490a8269976">Configures the Security Group to allow ports 2=
2, 80, and 443</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6a287f627ce9">SSH into the EC2 instance using the key pair</=
p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d806586557dd">Updates the system packages using <code>sudo a=
pt-get update &amp;&amp; sudo apt-get upgrade</code></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b7e0f4b9aba2">Installs required dependencies (curl, ca-certi=
ficates, postfix)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fd34e0420251">Adds the GitLab CE package repository using th=
e official script</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d19d67263c13">Sets the <code>EXTERNAL_URL</code> environment=
 variable to the EC2 public IP or DNS</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e1e5b546db3f">Installs GitLab CE using <code>sudo apt-get in=
stall gitlab-ce</code></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2383eff81cbe">Runs <code>sudo gitlab-ctl reconfigure</code> =
to apply configurations</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4354d4ea4bd2">Verifies all GitLab services are running using=
 <code>sudo gitlab-ctl status</code></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1e3f822c63a5">Opens the GitLab web interface in a browser us=
ing the EC2 public IP</p></li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"dba8a729c8a4"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"76e5277ae4aa">If port 80 is blocked: Reconfigure the Securit=
y Group to allow HTTP traffic</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"64baaba79e11">If installation fails: Check system resource a=
vailability (RAM minimum 4 GB required for GitLab CE)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c4cbed33e1e2">If external URL is misconfigured: Update <code=
>/etc/gitlab/gitlab.rb</code> and re-run <code>sudo gitlab-ctl reconfigure<=
/code></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4 local-id=3D"e7c83c3ac2b4" id=3D"Task22-RAD-3.2.2UseCase2:AdminLogintoGi=
tLabCE">3.2.2 Use Case 2: Admin Login to GitLab CE</h4>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5b5b671ab667"><strong>Description:</strong> The DevOps inter=
n logs in to the GitLab CE web interface using the initial root credentials=
 and changes the default password.</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a0cc2f3c0abd"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Intern, GitLab=
 CE Server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"150fecdf9b85"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e6b8debc6231">GitLab CE is successfully installed and web in=
terface is accessible</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9227cb9d0ed0">Initial root password file exists at <code>/et=
c/gitlab/initial_root_password</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"dc9550797452"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6220426007d5">DevOps intern is successfully logged in as roo=
t/admin</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4df75f9eb386">Default password has been changed to a secure =
password</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c4dbe62d33ce">GitLab dashboard is accessible</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1061b7819203"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d6c417926921">Open a browser and navigate to <code>http://&l=
t;EC2-Public-IP&gt;</code></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"49149a520246">GitLab login page is displayed</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"31f9fada62a6">Retrieve the initial root password from <code>=
/etc/gitlab/initial_root_password</code> on the server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"76de8ef1db33">Enter username as <code>root</code> and the re=
trieved initial password</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c2e5b270b289">Click Sign In</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e50ebeeb6fcf">GitLab prompts or allows navigation to change =
the root password</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8d9027bbbd66">Update the password to a secure custom passwor=
d</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d17b67fb9a6e">Re-login with the new credentials</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"436b60c02330">GitLab CE admin dashboard is displayed success=
fully</p></li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7a7e6987303c"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1d0d020666e1">If initial password file is not found: The fil=
e is only valid for 24 hours after installation; reset using <code>sudo git=
lab-rake "gitlab:password:reset[root]"</code></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3f12287d8c66">If login page is not reachable: Verify GitLab =
service status with <code>sudo gitlab-ctl status</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4 local-id=3D"7085f50ee30e" id=3D"Task22-RAD-3.2.3UseCase3:CreateaNewRepo=
sitory/ProjectinGitLabCE">3.2.3 Use Case 3: Create a New Repository/Project=
 in GitLab CE</h4>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c7886d0d7562"><strong>Description:</strong> The DevOps inter=
n creates a new GitLab project/repository to host the Flask Hello World app=
lication code.</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"db55bfb0bac8"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Intern, GitLab=
 CE Server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bcf48a53810d"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9d5a2b8f53d6">DevOps intern is logged in to GitLab CE as adm=
in or a valid user</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8b18a59de1db">GitLab CE is running and accessible</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9641341d9308"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9d6082c0febe">A new GitLab project named (e.g., <code>flask-=
hello-world</code>) is created</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2bf3d4607c56">The repository is initialized and ready to acc=
ept code pushes</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ee2afd84a520">Repository URL (HTTP and SSH) is available</p>=
</li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5189ff5e71bd"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"adab2279bdde">From the GitLab dashboard, click on "New Proje=
ct"</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5f91c6f48f4d">Select "Create blank project"</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2d1fb21b9043">Enter the project name as <code>flask-hello-wo=
rld</code></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4609b5b4301b">Set the visibility level (Private/Internal/Pub=
lic) as required</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"addd3c160df0">Optionally initialize the repository with a RE=
ADME</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"347755594f4b">Click "Create project"</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bd73ebcc9180">GitLab creates the repository and displays the=
 project page</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9bc0cc508917">Note down the repository clone URL (HTTP or SS=
H)</p></li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e266906de0ab"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"38a4d68fb849">If project name conflicts: Choose a unique pro=
ject name or namespace</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5d74bbeab82e">If using SSH: Ensure SSH public key is added t=
o the GitLab user profile under Settings &gt; SSH Keys before cloning/pushi=
ng</p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4 local-id=3D"fefe789addbc" id=3D"Task22-RAD-3.2.4UseCase4:CreateFlaskHel=
loWorldApplicationandPushtoGitLabCE">3.2.4 Use Case 4: Create Flask Hello W=
orld Application and Push to GitLab CE</h4>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2782de647e3b"><strong>Description:</strong> The DevOps inter=
n creates a simple Flask Hello World application locally, initializes a Git=
 repository, and pushes the code to the GitLab CE repository.</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"78a370b75cf2"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Intern, GitLab=
 CE Server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f9da84daf0c7"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"61c8479afd3b">GitLab CE repository (<code>flask-hello-world<=
/code>) is created and accessible</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bf19248ce614">Local machine or server has Git installed</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"79e56bc112fd">Python and pip are installed on the local mach=
ine/server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c98e99606c59">Network connectivity exists between local mach=
ine and EC2 instance</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5e6df18a4436"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c3c605137540">Flask Hello World application code is present =
in the GitLab CE repository</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"442646198834">Repository contents are visible in the GitLab =
web UI</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d00eac4cadbd">Commit history reflects the initial code push<=
/p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f84ca9fd370e"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9b82e0fa21ec">On the local machine, create a new directory: =
<code>mkdir flask-hello-world &amp;&amp; cd flask-hello-world</code></p></l=
i>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"baebd9698502">Create the Flask application file <code>app.py=
</code> with the following content:</p></li>
</ol></li>
</ul>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">
<pre class=3D"syntaxhighlighter-pre" data-syntaxhighlighter-params=3D"brush=
: java; gutter: false; theme: Confluence" data-theme=3D"Confluence">     fr=
om flask import Flask
     app =3D Flask(__name__)

     @app.route('/')
     def hello():
         return 'Hello World'

     if __name__ =3D=3D '__main__':
         app.run(debug=3DTrue)</pre>
</div>
</div>
<ol start=3D"3">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b47add6b7bc8">Create a <code>requirements.txt</code> file wi=
th <code>flask</code> listed as a dependency</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3b191ece3c39">Initialize a Git repository: <code>git init</c=
ode></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c2dbf9c56b24">Configure Git user details: <code>git config u=
ser.name</code> and <code>git config user.email</code></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ed4138fd7ac6">Stage all files: <code>git add .</code></p></l=
i>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"61f49975e661">Commit the changes: <code>git commit -m "Initi=
al commit: Flask Hello World app"</code></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"842d5b06130e">Add the GitLab CE remote URL: <code>git remote=
 add origin http://&lt;EC2-IP&gt;/root/flask-hello-world.git</code></p></li=
>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6914ac697248">Push the code to GitLab CE: <code>git push -u =
origin main</code> (or <code>master</code>)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"52fc13bb934d">Enter GitLab credentials when prompted</p></li=
>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"60c8e6c05b10">Navigate to the GitLab project in the browser =
and verify the code is visible</p></li>
</ol>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d6bb008953bc"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fdc2ac7b3ba5">If push is rejected due to branch name mismatc=
h: Use <code>git push -u origin HEAD</code> or rename the local branch with=
 <code>git branch -M main</code></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"123bbe1cb147">If authentication fails over HTTP: Use a Perso=
nal Access Token (PAT) instead of the root password by generating one from =
GitLab User Settings &gt; Access Tokens</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cdd9af819552">If using SSH push: Configure SSH key and use t=
he SSH remote URL format <code>git@&lt;EC2-IP&gt;:root/flask-hello-world.gi=
t</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h4 local-id=3D"7ac530884068" id=3D"Task22-RAD-3.2.5UseCase5:ValidatetheEnt=
ireSetup">3.2.5 Use Case 5: Validate the Entire Setup</h4>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"84295b59ed33"><strong>Description:</strong> The DevOps inter=
n validates that all components =E2=80=94 GitLab CE server, repository, and=
 pushed Flask code =E2=80=94 are functional and accessible.</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f4654d358b26"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Intern, GitLab=
 CE Server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d47857626ee7"><strong>Preconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"86e8082beef3">GitLab CE is running</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"01ac565ba79d">Repository is created</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4c57e085aa37">Flask code has been pushed</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ce2565d5323f"><strong>Postconditions:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"43e47f3f0ffd">All validation checks pass</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"9cd9d8869fc4">Screenshots and evidence are collected for del=
iverables</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f2b56d7497b6"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ccfdc0f152f2">Open the GitLab CE web interface and confirm t=
he dashboard loads</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8a70b6446c9f">Navigate to the <code>flask-hello-world</code>=
 project and confirm it is visible</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"18565d8d6926">Check the repository file listing to confirm <=
code>app.py</code> and <code>requirements.txt</code> are present</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fea769780255">Review the commit history to confirm the push =
was successful</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e72e41e80130">Optionally clone the repository on a different=
 directory and verify the code works by running <code>python app.py</code><=
/p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d87fa90ed0c6">Capture screenshots of the GitLab dashboard, p=
roject page, and repository files</p></li>
</ol></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"551309f5ae1e"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0cb134b0fca2">If the repository appears empty: Re-check the =
push command and confirm the correct remote URL was used</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7aa525f5a5dc">If the GitLab UI is not accessible: Verify EC2=
 instance is running and services are healthy with <code>sudo gitlab-ctl st=
atus</code></p></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"935621bb882a" id=3D"Task22-RAD-4.Non-FunctionalRequirements=
">4. Non-Functional Requirements</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"5551b22b497f" id=3D"Task22-RAD-4.1PerformanceRequirements">=
4.1 Performance Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a984e09f768d">The GitLab CE web interface should load within=
 5 seconds on a standard network connection</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"824958b41093">The EC2 instance should have a minimum of 4 GB=
 RAM and 2 vCPUs to ensure stable GitLab CE operation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b1b1401ef5ca">Git push and pull operations should complete w=
ithin 10 seconds for the small Flask application codebase</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"60c4e9c33268">GitLab CE services should start within 3 minut=
es of system boot</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"c74e9623100d" id=3D"Task22-RAD-4.2SecurityRequirements">4.2=
 Security Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7cec99ca51f6">The default root password must be changed imme=
diately after first login</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5d7a897bfcda">EC2 Security Groups must restrict SSH (port 22=
) access to known/trusted IP addresses only</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"13ea17472940">All GitLab repository access should require au=
thentication; anonymous access should be disabled for private repositories<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"14113f4c3c52">Personal Access Tokens (PAT) should be used fo=
r scripted or automated Git operations instead of plain passwords</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d5cb98012179">SSH keys should be used for secure Git operati=
ons wherever possible</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a6c7325df922">The EC2 instance OS should be kept updated wit=
h the latest security patches</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"a8904bca106b" id=3D"Task22-RAD-4.3UsabilityRequirements">4.=
3 Usability Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1a4c3cebee6e">The GitLab web interface must be accessible vi=
a a standard browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge) without requiring additional p=
lugins</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fa334ccce44b">The GitLab project page should clearly display=
 repository files, commit history, and clone URLs</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d94463257d75">Git remote configuration must follow standard =
Git conventions to ensure compatibility with common Git clients</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e5137f75ffb4">Documentation for setup steps should be clear =
enough for a team member with basic Linux and Git knowledge to follow</p></=
li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"982ab7b5a84c" id=3D"Task22-RAD-4.4ReliabilityRequirements">=
4.4 Reliability Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f5d2062089f5">GitLab CE services must remain stable after th=
e initial setup without requiring manual restarts</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b9fa4cbc1919">The EC2 instance should be configured to auto-=
start GitLab CE services on reboot using <code>sudo systemctl enable gitlab=
-runsvdir</code></p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"192dc54823b0">Git push operations must be idempotent =E2=80=
=94 re-pushing the same commits should not cause data loss or errors</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a6238d642cfa">The GitLab CE server must have a minimum uptim=
e of 99% during the duration of the internship task</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"47b8fd773887" id=3D"Task22-RAD-4.5ComplianceRequirements">4=
.5 Compliance Requirements</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c56a9a4aad70">GitLab CE is used under the MIT License; all u=
sage must comply with its terms</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7f3a93542ecf">AWS EC2 usage must comply with ABC Technologie=
s' cloud usage and cost management policies</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7c57dfc0455b">Any credentials (root password, PATs, SSH keys=
) must be handled in accordance with the organization's information securit=
y policy</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a87a27543411">The Flask application code pushed to GitLab mu=
st not contain any sensitive information such as API keys or passwords</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 local-id=3D"cca76ccba721" id=3D"Task22-RAD-5.AssumptionsandDependencies=
">5. Assumptions and Dependencies</h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"f8b880cf0fdd" id=3D"Task22-RAD-5.1Assumptions">5.1 Assumpti=
ons</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"02ebdda86e77">The DevOps intern has basic knowledge of Linux=
 command-line operations</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"aeab9ead5a63">The DevOps intern has access to an AWS account=
 with permissions to launch EC2 instances and configure Security Groups</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cc01bb11786f">The EC2 instance will use Ubuntu 20.04 LTS or =
22.04 LTS as the operating system</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6ad2ba471551">Internet connectivity is available on both the=
 EC2 instance and the local development machine</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d2dd546b1676">The GitLab CE version available in the officia=
l package repository is stable and production-ready for PoC purposes</p></l=
i>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"dda4daf8cda1">The Flask Hello World application is intended =
only for validation purposes and will not be deployed to production</p></li=
>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3cc722002a3d">Git is installed and configured on the local m=
achine used for code push</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 local-id=3D"0c0df9e4add0" id=3D"Task22-RAD-5.2Dependencies">5.2 Depende=
ncies</h3>
